            <crm:P78_is_identified_by>He succeeded his father King ʾIyāsu II in 1755. 
                  He was seven years old when he became a king and his grandmother, the famous Gondarian queen Bǝrhān Mogasā,  continued to act as his regent. 
                  Throughout his reign, he was only a figurehead and the real political power remained in the hand of the queen Bǝrhān Mogasā. 
               </crm:P78_is_identified_by>
